Main attention will be paid on recognition of cardiac arrest and on training of practical skills of cardiopulmonary resuscitation (CPR) on manikins. The students will be trained to perform different BLS simulation scenarios of common emergencies (bystander witnessed sudden cardiac arrest, respiratory arrest, seizures, drowning, car accident and severe trauma, foreign body in respiratory tract). After every simulation scenario debriefing will be held. Students learn to provide first aid for wounds, massive bleeding and bone fractures. Participation in practical sessions is mandatory.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To teach first aid and basic life support measures, so that student is able to provide first-aid as non-medical specialist.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completion of the course the student - is familiar with the main causes of life threatening conditions and acute illnesses - knows the principles of safety of lay rescuer and victim on the scene of accident, incl. person with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 - recognizes a patient in critical condition, incl. clinical death - is able to perform basic life support (BLS) for adults and children (incl. use of an AED) - is able to give first aid in life-threatening and potentially life-threatening conditions (foreign body airway obstruction, shock, disorders of consciousness, seizures, drowning, electric trauma, accidental hypothermia, heat illnesses, cardiovascular disease, poisonings, bites and stings, severe allergic reaction, bronchial asthma, emergency childbirth) - in the case of wounds is able to stop bleeding and cover the wound with sterile bandage      - is able to give first aid in massive bleeding and bone fractures  Because of COVID-19 pandemic this year on practical sessions students will not be taught artificial ventilation by mouth method and by pocket mask. The focus of BLS education will be on quality of chest compression without and with an AED. The student has to be able to open an airway and to perform one or two-person Ambu bag-mask techniques for manikin ventilation.
